The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Dec. 23: Cigarette manufacturers ITC and Godfrey Phillips India (GPI) have resumed production after getting directions from the government on what kind of pictorial warnings should be displayed on the packets. GPI vice-president (marketing) Neeta Kapur confirmed that the company had resumed production since Monday.                            
	 Mumbai, Dec. 23: The Reserve Bank today notified that lenders would provide loans only up to 80 per cent of the cost of property. This means, a home buyer will have to arrange at least 20 per cent of the property value on his own before seeking a loan from a bank.                            
	 Mumbai, Dec. 23: The State Bank of India today said it could seek restructuring of loans given to microfinance institutions (MFIs) if they turned non-performing, SBI chairman O.P. Bhatt said.                             
	 New Delhi, Dec. 23: The government will provide further incentives to the exporting sectors which are labour intensive such as handicraft as it has not fully recovered from last years slowdown, commerce minister Anand Sharma said.                             
	 New Delhi, Dec. 23: Civil aviation minister Praful Patel today met Prime Minister Manmohan Singh amid indications that the union cabinet is likely to decide on the much-awaited equity infusion worth Rs 1,200 crore in Air India soon.                                                                                                                          
